title: Concerning Virgins
creator: Saint Ambrose
description: Librivox recording of the Concerning virgins by Saint Ambrose. Read by Euthymius. Concerning Virgins (De Virginibus) is a series of letters, compiled into three “books,” St. Ambrose wrote to his sister, Manellia, These, perhaps Ambrose's earliest writings, were written in 377 CE. Written in a rather light-handed non-technical style they appear as ethical guides to women who are contemplating entering nunneries. More importantly, they set the tone for Ambrose's later writing on ethics. Concerning Virgins was referred to by other patristic writers including St. Jerome, St Augustine and Cassian, and are now included in the extra-biblical cannon of the early church fathers. (Summary by Gary Gilberd) For more free audiobooks, or to become a volunteer reader, please visit librivox.org. Download M4B (68MB)
